theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_eq_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    -- `interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A)`
    have hsubset : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      -- Because `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A`, taking closures preserves the inclusion.
      have : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      exact closure_mono this
    exact interior_mono hsubset
  ·
    -- `interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure (interior (closure A)))`
    have hsubset :
        (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆
          interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
      -- The set `interior (closure A)` is open and contained in `closure (interior (closure A))`.
      have h₁ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
        subset_closure
      exact interior_maximal h₁ isOpen_interior
    -- Since `interior (closure A)` is exactly the right-hand side, the inclusion gives the result.
    exact hsubset

theorem Topology.isClosed_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsClosed (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
  simpa using (isClosed_closure (s := interior (closure A)))
